features.name: NTP_transferase Catalyzes the formation of dTDP-glucose, from dTTP and glucose 1-phosphate, as well as its pyrophosphorolysis
dTDP_sugar_isom Catalyzes the epimerization of the C3' and C5'positions of dTDP-6-deoxy-D-xylo-4-hexulose, forming dTDP-6-deoxy-L-lyxo-4- hexulose
GDP_Man_Dehyd Belongs to the NAD(P)-dependent epimerase dehydratase family. dTDP-glucose dehydratase subfamily
RmlD_sub_bind Catalyzes the reduction of dTDP-6-deoxy-L-lyxo-4- hexulose to yield dTDP-L-rhamnose

BRCT,DNA_ligase_OB,DNA_ligase_ZBD,DNA_ligase_aden,HHH_2,HHH_5 DNA ligase that catalyzes the formation of phosphodiester linkages between 5'-phosphoryl and 3'-hydroxyl groups in double-stranded DNA using NAD as a coenzyme and as the energy source for the reaction. It is essential for DNA replication and repair of damaged DNA
